    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-9733",
      "publishedDate": "2026-06-23T07:05:20.564Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-06-23T07:05:20.564Z",
      "description": "Mojolicious::Plugin::Web::Auth::OAuth2 versions through 0.17 for Perl have an insecure default state parameter.\n\nWhen no state generator is specified in the constructor, the module defaults to using a SHA-1 hash of predictable and low-entropy sources, including the epoch time (which is leaked via the HTTP Date header) and a call to Perl's built-in rand function.\n\nA predictable state allows an attacker to hijack another user's session through cross site request forgery (CSRF).",
      "severity": "N/A",
      "references": [
        {
          "url": "https://metacpan.org/release/HAYAJO/Mojolicious-Plugin-Web-Auth-0.17/source/lib/Mojolicious/Plugin/Web/Auth/OAuth2.pm#L129-131",
          "type": "reference"
        },
        {
